Program: Outlook
Title: 06/01/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p005mzj1
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 7 Jan 2010
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Lucy Ash. Murder at sea; Angolans on the Africa Cup of Nations Lindy Robertson The dream yachting odyssey of a British couple turned into a nightmare when robbers boarded their boat off the coast of Thailand. Lindy Robertson tells Outlook how her husband was murdered, and how she managed to come through the ordeal. Angolans and the Africa Cup of Nations Not far from Luanda's new fifty-thousand seat football stadium, you'll find people living with no water, electricity or basic services. How do they feel about the huge expense of the tournament? Outlook's Louise Redvers talks to Joao, who runs a snack stall less than a kilometre from the stadium. Show less